{
  "texts": [
    "( 5) LoRA [13], where the lowrank decomposition is applied on attention layers with rank r = 4 and the adapter output scale (i.e., 4), which matches our MTLoRA hyperparameter.",
    "( 6) VL-Adapter [30], which shares an adapter across different tasks.",
    "( 7) Hyperformer [24], where a hyper-network is used to produce the weights for adapters for various tasks.",
    "(8) Polyhistor [22], where decomposed hyper-networks are used to share information across different tasks while still necessitating separate training and inference paths for each task.",
    "Quantitative AnalysisFor a fair comparison, MTLoRA, MTLoRA+, as well as all other baselines, are all based on the Swin-Tiny variant of the Swin Transformers family of models [23]."
  ]
}